(b) Oxbow Reservation. The decision to postpone or not proceed with the Closing of the Share purchase as outlined in Section 1, remains at the sole discretion of Oxbow and shall only be exercised upon fulfillment of any one of the following conditions stated in this Section 6(b):

1. If Oxbow determines that all contractual obligations have been met by both parties;
2. If Oxbow finds no material adverse change or effect on the business, assets, liabilities, or financial condition of the company being sold;
3. If Oxbow receives satisfactory legal and financial due diligence materials from the selling party;
4. If Oxbow obtains necessary financing for the purchase;
5. If all regulatory approvals required have been obtained or waived;
6. If Oxbow is satisfied with the representations, warranties, covenants, and other agreements of the selling party contained in this Agreement;
7. If Oxbow deems it advisable to close after considering any other relevant factors that may impact the transaction.
